            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"title1\">一　冯·赖特的广义模态逻辑构想</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003260": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003260",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">既然是“十五讲”，我们就不必那么拘谨，在讲冯·赖特（G. H. von Wright）的有关思想之前，先说说他这个人吧。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003261": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003261",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">冯·赖特是20世纪著名的逻辑学家和哲学家，已于2003年6月4日去世。从1996年开始，我与这位重要人物发生了密切交往，甚至建立了某种私人友谊。1997年9月至1998年9月，我在芬兰赫尔辛基大学跟从他做访问学者一年；我接到他的最后一封信是2003年2月20日，距他最后去世仅132天。我在一些论著中曾这样描述他：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003262": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003262",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\"><br class=\"calibre2\"></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003263": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003263",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">冯·赖特，1916年6月14日出生于芬兰赫尔辛基一个说瑞典语的贵族家庭。1934年入赫尔辛基大学，1937年大学毕业后攻读博士学位。1941年获哲学博士学位。1946年任赫尔辛基大学教授。在1939年和1947年两度赴英国剑桥大学，前一次是作为研究生访学，后一次是应邀作学术讲演，在此期间与在剑桥任教的维特根斯坦发生密切交往，并深获他的信任。1947年，当维特根斯坦辞去剑桥教授职位时，他推荐冯·赖特继任，并获得批准。当时冯·赖特年仅31岁。在任职三年多之后，冯·赖特辞职返回芬兰，任赫尔辛基大学哲学系教授。1951年，维特根斯坦去世，指定冯·赖特为他的三位遗嘱执行人之一。此后，冯·赖特先后担任过美国康奈尔大学教授，芬兰科学院研究教授、院长等职。其研究领域涉及归纳逻辑、哲学逻辑、伦理学、一般价值和规范的理论、行动理论、人文科学方法论、文化哲学、心灵哲学、维特根斯坦研究等。先后用英语、德语、芬兰语、瑞典语等语种出版专著、论文集近30种，其中有些著作又被译为法语、俄语、意大利语、西班牙语、日语、汉语等语种出版，其学术研究的特点是融通分析哲学和欧洲大陆哲学。他是哲学逻辑和维特根斯坦研究方面公认的国际权威，但其思想却具有浓厚的人文主义意味，特别是中晚期更是明显偏向人文主义研究。正如哈贝马斯所评价的，他是一位“处于分析传统和诠释学传统之间的人物”。他的研究成果产生了广泛的国际性影响，并给他带来很高的国际性声誉：先后被授予近20个博士或名誉博士学位，是15个国家、地区或跨国科学院的院士，并曾任国际哲学学院主席，国际科学史和科学哲学联合会逻辑、方法论和科学哲学分会会长。1989年，美国《在世哲学家文库》出版了《冯·赖特哲学》卷，此书编者指出：“本丛书的冯·赖特哲学卷不需要任何辩护。在过去几十年中，冯·赖特已经成为世界范围内哲学家关注的中心。”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003264": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003264",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\"><br class=\"calibre2\"></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003265": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003265",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">通过研读他的著述，我也逐渐理清了冯·赖特的学术理路和思想进程：早年受其博士学位导师、当时的芬兰哲学领袖埃洛·凯拉（Eino Kaila）的影响，信奉逻辑经验主义，研究归纳概率逻辑。他用充分条件和必要条件等术语重新阐释了培根、密尔等人提出的排除归纳法，这种新表述已经进入当代的许多逻辑教科书。在50年代前后研究逻辑真理时，偶然发现量词、模态词、道义词、时态词、认知态度词之间的类似，由此提出广义模态逻辑的系统构想，并创立了道义逻辑、优先逻辑这样一些新的逻辑分支。在研究道义逻辑的过程中，认识到义务、允许、禁止等一方面与道德规范和法律规范相关，另一方面与人的行动和行为相关，由此导致他对伦理学、一般价值和规范理论和行动理论的研究。对后面这些理论研究的结果，又进一步导致他研究人文社会科学方法论与自然科学方法论的联系与区别，提出了因果论解释模式和意向论解释模式之间的二元对立，并重点研究了意向论解释模式。晚年，他又研究心灵哲学和文化哲学，作为公共知识分子向社会发言，对工业技术文明总体上持批评态度，倡导一种人文主义的生活方式。此外，作为维特根斯坦的遗嘱执行人，他在维氏遗著的搜寻、整理、编辑、出版等方面做了大量工作，并对其思想做了一些研究，为他在国际哲学界赢得了广泛声誉和重要地位。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003266": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003266",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\"><br class=\"calibre2\"></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003267": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003267",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">从阅读他的著作和与他的个人接触中，我对冯·赖特教授获得了这样的个人印象：整个说来，冯·赖特不是像尼采和叔本华那样在学术领域内锋芒毕露、横冲直撞的斗士，不是那种给人以情感的冲击和心灵的震撼的思想家，而是一位稳健、儒雅、勤勉的学者，一位分析型技术型的哲学家，一位学术圈里的绅士，其睿智、深邃、平和犹如晚年的歌德。在评述他人观点时，他相当周详和平实，很少做惊人之论；对自己的思想则给予全面、细致、常常是技术化的论证。感觉起来，他的写作风格就像一道山涧小溪，流淌得非常自然、平静、舒缓，沁人心脾，启人深思。读他的书也许不会激活你的血液，却会给你“润物细无声”的春雨般的滋润。——这就是我所获得的关于冯·赖特的真实感受。<sup class=\"suptext1\"><$link to=\"$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003616\">〔1〕</$link></sup></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003268": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003268",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\"><br class=\"calibre2\"></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003269": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003269",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">顺便说一下，我对冯·赖特的人格特质和学术工作的评价，得到冯·赖特本人的极大认可，他在其自传中引用了上述某些文字。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003270": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003270",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">还有必要预先澄清一些概念。在逻辑学中，像“必然”、“可能”、“不可能”这样的词叫做“模态词”，分别用符号“□”、“◇”、“⇁◇”来表示；含有模态词的命题叫做“模态命题”。像“应该”、“允许”、“禁止”这样的词叫做“道义词”，分别用大写字母“O”、“P”、“F”表示，含道义模态词的命题叫做“道义命题”。英语中的句子都有时态因素，如“过去”、“将来”以及“过去一直”和“将要永远”，通常用大写字母“P”、“F”、“H”、“G”表示，含上述时态因素的命题叫做“时态命题”。至于像“知道”、“相信”这样的认知动词，用大写字母“K”（英文词know的首字母）、“B”（英文词believe的首字母）表示，含有认知动词的命题叫做“认知命题”。由于道义词、时态词和认知动词等等在一些重要特性上与模态词相类似，它们一起被叫做“广义模态词”。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003271": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003271",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">我们现在可以谈一谈冯·赖特关于广义模态逻辑的构想。1949年初的某一天，当时任剑桥大学哲学教授的冯·赖特在散步时，忽然想到：模态词“可能”、“不可能”和“必然”之间的关系，完全类似于量词“有些”、“无一”、“所有”之间的关系。例如：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003272": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003272",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\"><br class=\"calibre2\"></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003273": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003273",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">（1）∀xA（x）↔<$image alt=\"alt\" class=\"tpzz\" source=\"$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/images/images/00002.jpeg\"></$image>∃x<$image alt=\"alt\" class=\"tpzz\" source=\"$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/images/images/00002.jpeg\"></$image>A（x）</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003274": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003274",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">（2）∃xA（x）↔<$image alt=\"alt\" class=\"tpzz\" source=\"$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/images/images/00002.jpeg\"></$image>∀x<$image alt=\"alt\" class=\"tpzz\" source=\"$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/images/images/00002.jpeg\"></$image>A（x）</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003275": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003275",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">（3）∀x<$image alt=\"alt\" class=\"tpzz\" source=\"$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/images/images/00002.jpeg\"></$image>A（x）↔<$image alt=\"alt\" class=\"tpzz\" source=\"$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/images/images/00002.jpeg\"></$image>∃xA（x）</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003276": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003276",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">（4）<$image alt=\"alt\" class=\"tpzz\" source=\"$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/images/images/00002.jpeg\"></$image>∀xA（x）↔∃x<$image alt=\"alt\" class=\"tpzz\" source=\"$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/images/images/00002.jpeg\"></$image>A（x）</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003277": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003277",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">（6）∀xA（x）→A（x／t），若t对于x代入自由</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003278": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003278",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">（7）A（x／t）→∃xA（x），若t对于x代入自由</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003279": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003279",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">（8）∀xA（x）→∃xA（x）</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003280": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003280",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\"><br class=\"calibre2\"></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003281": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003281",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext4\">这里，（1）和（2）表明，全称量词和存在量词可以相互定义：“所有x满足公式A”等值于“并非有些x不满足公式A”，“有些x满足公式A”等值于“并非有些x不满足公式A”。如果在（1）—（8）中，把“∀x”换成“□”，把“∃x”换成“◇”，并且把“A（x）”或“A（x／t）”换成“p”，新得到的（1）—（8）的变体仍然成立。例如，“□p”等值于“<$image alt=\"alt\" class=\"tpzz\" source=\"$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/images/images/00002.jpeg\"></$image>◇<$image alt=\"alt\" class=\"tpzz\" source=\"$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/images/images/00002.jpeg\"></$image>p”，“◇p”等值于“<$image alt=\"alt\" class=\"tpzz\" source=\"$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/images/images/00002.jpeg\"></$image>□<$image alt=\"alt\" class=\"tpzz\" source=\"$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/images/images/00002.jpeg\"></$image>p”，如此等等。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003282": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003282",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">稍后，冯·赖特还发现，不仅量词和模态词之间存在类似，而且在它们与道义概念“应该”、“允许”、“禁止”之间，以及与认知概念“证实”、“不确定”、“证伪”之间，也存在着相应的类似。于是，至少应该有四个独立的逻辑学分支：存在逻辑即量词逻辑、真势逻辑（alethic logic）、道义逻辑（deontic logic）和认知逻辑（epistemic logic）。他于1951年出版《模态逻辑》一书。这本仅90页的小册子包含以下四个基本观点：（1）在模态词和量词之间存在着完全的类似；（2）利用这种类似，可以把适用于部分量词理论的判定程序推广到各种模态逻辑系统中；（3）可以利用分配范式定义模态逻辑中的逻辑真理；（4）探讨模态概念的不同解释，以便建立包括道义、认知、价值论概念在内的一般模态理论。上述观点或做法一再重复出现于码·赖特的哲学逻辑研究中，成为他的哲学逻辑工作的一大特色。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003283": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003283",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">因此，冯·赖特给出了下表中除时间论之外的部分：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003284": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003284",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"picture\"><$image alt=\"alt\" class=\"calibre3\" source=\"$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/images/images/00069.jpeg\"></$image></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003285": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003285",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">在这一思想的激励下，道义逻辑、认知逻辑（知道逻辑、相信逻辑、问题逻辑、断定逻辑等）、时态逻辑等广义模态逻辑分支后来得到迅速发展，模态逻辑本身则被叫做（真性）模态逻辑。所有这些逻辑都是在经典逻辑的基础上，加入新的逻辑常项，加入新的公式，以及与这些常项相关的新的公理和推理规则而构成的系统，所有的经典逻辑定理都是这些系统的定理，此外还包含许多与新常项有关的定理。因此，相对于经典逻辑而言，这些逻辑被叫做“扩充逻辑”（extended logics），相应的逻辑系统被叫做经典逻辑系统的“扩充系统”（extended systems）。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003286": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003286",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">不过，应该强调指出，广义模态逻辑并非自冯·赖特才开始。实际上，早在亚里士多德那里，就开始了对模态逻辑的系统研究。在《解释篇》中，亚氏研究了模态命题及其相互之间的真值关系；在《前分析篇》中，用于研究模态三段论的篇幅远远大于研究直言三段论的篇幅。在欧洲中世纪，对广义模态逻辑也有比较系统的研究。冯·赖特只是在现代逻辑的语境中，系统地阐发了广义模态逻辑的构想，并身体力行，做出了一些实际的工作，例如创立了道义逻辑，产生了较大的影响。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003287": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003287",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"title1\">二　模态词和模态逻辑</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003288": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003288",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">模态词“必然”（□）、“可能”（◇）、“不可能”（<$image alt=\"alt\" class=\"tpzz\" source=\"$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/images/images/00002.jpeg\"></$image>◇）可以附着在一个完整命题（简单命题或复合命题）之前，修饰、限制该命题，这时叫做“从言模态”（de dicto modality）。例如：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003289": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003289",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（1）必然地（如果物体受到摩擦，物体就会生热）。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003290": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003290",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（2）可能地（明天既刮风又下雨）。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003291": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003291",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（3）不可能（人拔着自己的头发上天）。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003292": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003292",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext4\">分别可以符号化为：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003293": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003293",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（1′）□（p→q）</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003294": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003294",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（2′）◇（r∧s）</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003295": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003295",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（3′）<$image alt=\"alt\" class=\"tpzz\" source=\"$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/images/images/00002.jpeg\"></$image>◇t</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003296": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003296",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">模态词也可以插入句子成分之间，修饰主词和谓词之间的联系方式，这时叫做“从物模态”（de re modality）。例如：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003297": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003297",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（4）所有的人都必然是有理性的。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003298": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003298",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（5）有些北大学生可能成为国家栋梁。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003299": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003299",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（6）所有生物都不可能长生不死。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003300": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003300",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext4\">分别可以符号化为：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003301": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003301",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（4′）∀x（P（x）→□R（x））</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003302": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003302",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（5′）∃x（B（x）∧◇D（x））</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003303": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003303",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（6′）∀（S（x）→<$image alt=\"alt\" class=\"tpzz\" source=\"$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/images/images/00002.jpeg\"></$image>◇M（x））</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003304": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003304",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">从言模态属于模态命题逻辑的研究范围，从言模态则属于词项逻辑和谓词逻辑的研究范围。无论是模态命题逻辑还是模态谓词逻辑，都是在经典逻辑的基础上，用模态词□和◇对后者的语言作必要的扩充，并引入与□和◇相关的公理和变形规则而构成的，因而都是经典逻辑的扩充系统。本书只简单讲解模态命题逻辑，下面给出它的一个一般性定义，其中“∈”表示某个元素属于某个集合：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003305": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003305",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\"><br class=\"calibre2\"></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003306": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003306",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">D1　一个模态命题逻辑S是经典命题逻辑重言式集的扩集，扩集满足以下条件：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003307": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003307",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">（1）□（α→β）→（□α→□β）∈S；</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003308": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003308",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">（2）S在分离规则下封闭：若α∈S，α→β∈S，则β∈S；</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003309": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003309",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">（3）S在弱必然化规则下封闭：若α是重言式，则□α∈S；</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003310": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003310",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">（4）S在必然化规则下封闭：若α∈S，则□α∈S。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003311": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003311",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\"><br class=\"calibre2\"></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003312": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003312",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">若一个模态系统满足（1）—（3），则称它是古典模态逻辑；若一个模态系统满足（1）、（2）和（4），则称它为正规模态逻辑。是否具有必然化规则（记为N），是正规系统区别于非正规系统的主要标志。N是说：如果一个公式是某系统内可证公式，则它是逻辑必然的。只满足上面（1）、（2）和（4）的模态系统是正规的，并且是极小正规的，其他正规系统都是在极小正规系统上做某种添加得到的。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003313": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003313",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">下面给出的模态系统都以分离规则（MP）和必然化规则作推理规则，并以下面的某些公式作公理：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003314": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003314",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\"><br class=\"calibre2\"></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003315": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003315",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">A<sub class=\"calibre7\">0</sub>　所有命题逻辑的重言式</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003316": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003316",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">A<sub class=\"calibre7\">1</sub>　◇α↔<$image alt=\"alt\" class=\"tpzz\" source=\"$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/images/images/00002.jpeg\"></$image>□<$image alt=\"alt\" class=\"tpzz\" source=\"$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/images/images/00002.jpeg\"></$image>α</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003317": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003317",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">K　□（α→β）→（□α→□β）</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003318": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003318",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">D　□α→◇α</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003319": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003319",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">T　□α→α</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003320": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003320",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">4　□α→□□α</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003321": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003321",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">E　◇α→□◇α</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003322": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003322",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">B　α→□◇α</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003323": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003323",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">Tr　□α↔α</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003324": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003324",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\"><br class=\"calibre2\"></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003325": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003325",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">这里，A<sub class=\"calibre8\">1</sub>表示，“可能α”等值于“并非必然非α”；K表示“必然”对“蕴涵”的分配律：如果必然地α蕴涵β，那么，必然α蕴涵必然β；D表示：凡是必然的都是可能的；T表示，凡是必然的都是现实的；4、E、B涉及模态词的重叠。4表示：如果必然α，则必然必然α；E表示，如果可能α，则必然可能α；B表示：如果α是真的，则必然可能α。Tr表示：必然α等值于α。加入Tr的系统含有模态词，但其模态词实际上是多余的，因为含模态词的命题实质上等于不含模态词的命题，这样的模态系统“坍塌”（collapse）为非模态系统。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003326": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003326",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">由此可以定义一批模态逻辑系统如下（其中粗体字母表示某个公式的名称，非粗体字母表示相应系统的名称）：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003327": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003327",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\"><br class=\"calibre2\"></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003328": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003328",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">A<sub class=\"calibre7\">0</sub>＋A<sub class=\"calibre7\">1</sub>＋K＋MP＋N＝K＝极小正规模态逻辑系统</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003329": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003329",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">K＋D＝D</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003330": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003330",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">K＋T＝T＝哥德尔／费斯／冯·赖特系统</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003331": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003331",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">K＋T＋4＝S<sub class=\"calibre7\">4</sub></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003332": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003332",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">K＋T＋B＝B＝布劳维尔系统</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003333": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003333",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">K＋T＋4＋B＝K＋T＋4＋E＝S<sub class=\"calibre7\">5</sub></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003334": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003334",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">K＋Tr＝不足道系统</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003335": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003335",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\"><br class=\"calibre2\"></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003336": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003336",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">在这些系统中，常见的正规模态命题逻辑系统是K、D、T、B、S<sub class=\"calibre8\">4</sub>和S<sub class=\"calibre8\">5</sub>。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003337": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003337",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">在如上构造的模态逻辑系统T以及比T强的系统中，可以证明如下的模态对当方阵所示的各种关系：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003338": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003338",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"picture\"><$image alt=\"alt\" class=\"calibre3\" source=\"$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/images/images/00070.jpeg\"></$image></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003339": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003339",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">根据这个对当方阵，各种模态命题之间有以下推理关系：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003340": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003340",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（1）“必然p”推出“并非必然非p”；</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003341": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003341",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（2）“必然非p”推出“并非必然p”；</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003342": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003342",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（3）“必然p”推出“可能p”；</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003343": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003343",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（4）“并非可能p”推出“并非必然p”；</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003344": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003344",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（5）“必然非p”推出“可能非p”；</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003345": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003345",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（6）“并非可能非p”推出“并非必然非p”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003346": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003346",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（7）“必然p”等值于“并非可能非p”；</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003347": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003347",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（8）“必然非p”等值于“并非可能p”；</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003348": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003348",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（9）“可能p”等值于“并非必然非p”；</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003349": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003349",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（10）“可能非p”等值于“并非必然p”。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003350": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003350",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（11）“不可能p”等值于“必然非p”。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003351": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003351",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">请看下面的例题：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003352": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003352",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\"><br class=\"calibre2\"></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003353": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003353",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">例1　一把钥匙能打开天下所有的锁。这样的万能钥匙是不可能存在的。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003354": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003354",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">以下哪项最符合题干的断定？</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003355": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003355",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">A．任何钥匙都必然有它打不开的锁。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003356": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003356",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">B．至少有一把钥匙必然打不开天下所有的锁。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003357": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003357",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">C．至少有一把锁天下所有的钥匙都必然打不开。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003358": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003358",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">D．任何钥匙都可能有它打不开的锁。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003359": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003359",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">E．至少有一把钥匙可能打不开天下所有的锁。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003360": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003360",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\"><br class=\"calibre2\"></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003361": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003361",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext4\">解析：答案是A。因为“不可能一把钥匙能打开天下所有的锁”等值于“必然地并非一把钥匙能打开天下所有的锁”，后者又等值于“必然地任何钥匙都有它打不开的锁”，即选项A：“任何钥匙都必然有它打不开的锁。”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003362": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003362",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\"><br class=\"calibre2\"></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003363": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003363",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">例2　美国先总统林肯说过：“最高明的骗子，可能在某个时刻欺骗所有的人，也可能在所有时刻欺骗某些人，但不可能在所有时刻欺骗所有的人。”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003364": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003364",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">如果林肯的上述断定是真的，那么下述哪项断定是假的？</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003365": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003365",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">A．林肯可能在某个时刻受骗。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003366": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003366",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">B．林肯可能在任何时候都不受骗。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003367": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003367",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">C．骗子也可能在某个时刻受骗。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003368": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003368",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">D．不存在某个时刻所有的人都必然不受骗。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003369": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003369",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">E．不存在某一时刻有人可能不受骗。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003370": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003370",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\"><br class=\"calibre2\"></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003371": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003371",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext4\">解析：答案是E。选项A和C都可以从“骗子可能在某个时刻欺骗所有的人，也可能在所有时刻欺骗某些人”推出；D等于是说“在所有时刻有些人可能受骗”，显然也可从题干中推出；B可以从“不可能在所有时刻欺骗所有的人”推出；E等于是说“在所有时刻所有人都必然受骗”，这与题干所说的“不可能在所有时刻欺骗所有的人”相矛盾，因此E是假的。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003372": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003372",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\"><br class=\"calibre2\"></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003373": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003373",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">例3　依次取n个（n＞1）自然数组成一有穷数列，其中的奇数数列和偶数数列显然都比该自然数数列短。但是，假如让该自然数数列无限延长，则其中的奇数数列和偶数数列就会与自然数数列本身一样长。由此我们可以作出结论：在有穷的世界里，部分必定小于整体；在无穷的世界里，部分可能等于整体。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003374": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003374",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">下面哪一项不可能是上面结论的逻辑推论？</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003375": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003375",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">A．在有穷的世界里，部分可能小于整体。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003376": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003376",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">B．在无穷的世界里，部分必然不等于整体。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003377": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003377",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">C．在无穷的世界里，整体可能等于部分。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003378": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003378",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">D．在有穷的世界里，整体必定大于部分。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003379": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003379",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">E．在无穷的世界里，并非部分不可能等于整体。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003380": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003380",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\"><br class=\"calibre2\"></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003381": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003381",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext4\">解析：答案是B。既然在有穷的世界里，部分必定小于整体，根据从“必然”推“可能”的规则，显然可以推出“部分可能小于整体”；根据“小于”、“大于”关系的性质，显然也可推出“整体必定大于部分”。既然在无穷的世界里，部分可能等于整体，显然可以推出“整体可能等于部分”；根据“必然”和“不可能”的关系，也可以推出“并非部分不可能等于整体”；但无论如何，不可能推出其矛盾命题“部分必然不等于整体”。所以，从题干不可能得到的逻辑结论是选项B。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003382": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003382",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">构造模态谓词逻辑有两种方法：一是以谓词演算作基础，加入模态词□和◇以及上面列举的某个或某些模态公式，得到模态谓词逻辑系统，这叫做量化逻辑的模态扩充。前面已经把谓词演算记为Q，则Q＋K、Q＋K＋D、Q＋K＋T、Q＋K＋T＋B、Q＋K＋T＋4、Q＋K＋T＋4＋B就分别是相应于模态命题逻辑系统K、D、T、B、S<sub class=\"calibre8\">4</sub>和S<sub class=\"calibre8\">5</sub>的模态谓词逻辑系统。二是以模态命题逻辑系统作基础，用谓词演算的语言和公理对它们作扩充，得到模态谓词逻辑系统，这叫做模态命题逻辑的量化扩充。这两种办法得到的最终结果是等价的。有些正规模态谓词逻辑系统中包含著名的巴坎（Bacan Marcus）公式：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003383": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003383",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">BF　（∀x）□F（x）→□（∀x）F（x）</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003384": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003384",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">通常把这些系统记法中的Q省略掉，简记为K＋BF，D＋BF，T＋BF，S<sub class=\"calibre8\">4</sub>＋BF，S<sub class=\"calibre8\">5</sub>＋BF等。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003385": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003385",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"title1\">三　可能世界语义学</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003386": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003386",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">莱布尼茨最先提出了“可能世界”概念，并基于这一概念阐发了一些重要思想。他认为，一个事态α是可能的，当且仅当α不包含逻辑矛盾。一个由事态α<sub class=\"calibre8\">1</sub>，α<sub class=\"calibre8\">2</sub>，α<sub class=\"calibre8\">3</sub>…形成的组合是可能的，当且仅当α<sub class=\"calibre8\">1</sub>，α<sub class=\"calibre8\">2</sub>，α<sub class=\"calibre8\">3</sub>…推不出逻辑矛盾。由无穷多的具有各种性质的事物所形成的可能的事物的组合，就是一个可能世界。有许许多多的可能世界，例如现实世界就是一个可能世界，它是由上帝选择的一个最丰富、最完美的可能世界。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003387": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003387",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">莱布尼茨进而利用可能世界去讨论必然性、可能性、偶然性等问题，他认为：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003388": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003388",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">L<sub class=\"calibre8\">1</sub>　一命题是必然的，当且仅当它在所有可能世界中都是真的；</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003389": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003389",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">L<sub class=\"calibre8\">2</sub>　一命题是可能的，当且仅当它在有些可能世界中是真的。他还把真理分为两大类：推理的真理和事实的真理，推理的真理就是在所有的可能世界中都真的真理，因而是必然的；事实的真理是只在现实世界中为真的真理，因而是偶然的。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003390": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003390",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">20世纪50—60年代，鉴于模态逻辑发展的迫切需要，以克里普克（Saul Kripke）为代表的一批逻辑学家从莱布尼茨的上述思想出发，发展了一种模态语义理论即可能世界语义学。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003391": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003391",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">什么是可能世界？主要有两种定义或说明方式：一种是：“可能世界包括我们能想象的任何世界，也就是我们能想象的任何一个世界都是可能世界。我们的现实世界只是可能世界中的一个。”例如，《西游记》所描写的那个世界就是一个可能世界，其中写了孙悟空、猪八戒、沙和尚这三位弟子护卫唐僧师父到西天取经的故事；神话、小说、科幻作品、童话等等所描写的世界都是可能世界。另一种是：可能世界是逻辑上一致的世界，即任何不包含逻辑矛盾的世界都是可能世界。这是逻辑学所要求的可能世界，不满足这一要求的可能世界是不可理喻的，不能作为刻画其他逻辑概念的基础。现实世界则是我们构想其他可能世界的根据和基础，给出不同于现实世界的其他可能世界通常有以下几种方法：在某个可能世界中，（1）某一现实事物不存在，或者某一非现实事物存在；或者（2）某物所具有的性质不同于此物在现实世界中具有的性质，或者（3）某些事物之间的关系不同于这些事物在现实世界中的关系；或者（4）某些现实发生的事件在其中不发生，或者某些现实不发生的事件在其中发生，如此等等。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003392": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003392",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">相对于经典语义学和莱布尼茨的思想而言，可能世界语义学作了几个重大的改进，具体来说：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003393": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003393",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">第一，它使命题的真假相对化。由于经典语义学（隐含地）是相对于现实世界而言的，因此其公式的真假只是在现实世界中的真假，它就没有必要特别指明此公式在现实世界中真，彼公式在现实世界中假，而可以抽象地、一般地谈论公式的真假。而在模态逻辑中，我们所面对的是各种各样的可能世界，它们之间是有某种差异的：一个体可以在一可能世界中存在，但并不在另一可能世界中存在；一事件可以在一个可能世界中发生，但不在另一个可能世界中发生。于是，描述或反映该个体或事件的命题就有可能在一个可能世界中真，但在另一个可能世界中假。这样，我们不再能够抽象地一般地谈论一个命题的真假，命题的真假是相对于特定的可能世界而言的，给一个命题赋值必须注明是在哪个可能世界之中。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003394": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003394",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">第二，它使必然性、可能性概念相对化。由于必然性、可能性概念是由命题的真假定义的，既然后者是相对于特定的可能世界而言的，前者因此也就是相对于特定的可能世界而言的。我们不能再抽象地、一般地谈论必然性、可能性，而只能谈论在某一特定的可能世界中的必然性和可能性；我们不能再一般地说某一命题是必然的或可能的，而只能说，某一命题在某一特定的可能世界中是必然的或可能的。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003395": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003395",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">第三，它使可能世界之间具有一定的关系，叫做“可通达关系”（accessibility relation）。命题α在一可能世界中是必然的，不再要求它无限制地在所有的可能世界中真，而只要求它在该可能世界可通达的所有可能世界中是真的。如果某些可能世界与该世界没有可通达关系，即使α在那些可能世界中假，α在那个世界中仍然可以是必然的；但是，假如α在该世界可通达的有的可能世界中假，则α在该世界中就不再是必然的。世界w<sub class=\"calibre8\">i</sub>可以通达到世界w<sub class=\"calibre8\">j</sub>，记为w<sub class=\"calibre8\">i</sub>Rw<sub class=\"calibre8\">j</sub>，其直观意思是：w<sub class=\"calibre8\">i</sub>可以演变为w<sub class=\"calibre8\">j</sub>，w<sub class=\"calibre8\">j</sub>相对于w<sub class=\"calibre8\">i</sub>来说是可能的，如目前有核武器的世界可以演变为没有核武器的世界，也可以演变为使地球毁灭的世界。在可能世界语义学中，R实际上是W的元素之间的一种真值关系，用可能世界语义学的专门术语来说，它满足下面两个条件：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003396": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003396",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\"><br class=\"calibre2\"></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003397": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003397",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">V（□α，w<sub class=\"calibre7\">i</sub>）＝1，当且仅当，∀w<sub class=\"calibre7\">j</sub>（w<sub class=\"calibre7\">i</sub>Rw<sub class=\"calibre7\">j</sub>＝＞V（α，w<sub class=\"calibre7\">j</sub>）＝1）；</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003398": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003398",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">V（◇α，w<sub class=\"calibre7\">i</sub>）＝1，当且仅当，∃w<sub class=\"calibre7\">j</sub>（w<sub class=\"calibre7\">i</sub>Rw<sub class=\"calibre7\">j</sub>并且V（α，w<sub class=\"calibre7\">j</sub>）＝1）。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003399": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003399",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\"><br class=\"calibre2\"></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003400": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003400",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext4\">这两个定义已经把如上所述的莱布尼茨对必然性和可能性的说明弱化了，用更通俗的话来说，其意思是：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003401": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003401",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\"><br class=\"calibre2\"></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003402": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003402",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">L<sub class=\"calibre8\">1</sub>　□α在可能世界w<sub class=\"calibre8\">i</sub>上是真的，当且仅当，在w<sub class=\"calibre8\">i</sub>可通达的所有可能世界w<sub class=\"calibre8\">j</sub>上，α是真的；</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003403": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003403",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">L<sub class=\"calibre8\">2</sub>　◇α在可能世界w<sub class=\"calibre8\">i</sub>上是真的，当且仅当，在w<sub class=\"calibre8\">i</sub>可通达的有些可能世界w<sub class=\"calibre8\">j</sub>上，α是真的。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003404": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003404",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">可能世界语义学通过模型方法将上述思想形式地刻画出来，在此从略。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003405": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003405",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">可能世界语义学为模态逻辑提供了十分适用的语义工具，它可以合理地刻画各种模态命题如“必然α”、“可能α”、“不可能α”等等的真值条件，从而也就能够刻画这些命题之间的推理关系，并且也能够讨论模态逻辑系统的各种元逻辑特性，如可靠性和完全性等，这样就把模态逻辑奠定在一个合理且坚实的基础上，它的发展由此进入到一个新的阶段。在当代逻辑学体系中，模态逻辑已经获得了“新经典逻辑”的地位。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003406": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003406",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">可能世界语义学还在哲学逻辑的广大领域，例如在道义逻辑、时态逻辑、认识论逻辑、反事实条件句逻辑、一般内涵逻辑等等中获得了成功的应用，当然要作一些必要的改变。它甚至还适用于经典逻辑，也可以把经典逻辑语义学作为特例包含在自身之中。这恰好符合我们对于可能世界的直观理解：可能世界就是不包含逻辑矛盾的世界，也就是经典逻辑规律在其中成立的世界。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003407": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003407",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">可能世界语义学的意义甚至远远超出了逻辑领域，而在当代哲学中获得广泛应用。可以这样说，在分析和探讨意义和指称问题、真理问题以及某些认识论问题，例如先验命题与后验命题、分析命题和综合命题、必然命题和偶然命题的传统区分时，不接触到可能世界语义学的概念和思想，在当代哲学中几乎是不可能的。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003408": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003408",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"title1\">四　道义逻辑</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003409": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003409",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">如前所述，在逻辑学中，把“义务”、“允许”、“禁止”这样的词叫做“道义模态词”，含道义模态词的命题叫做“道义命题”。所谓“道义逻辑”，就是研究道义命题的逻辑特性及其推理关系的逻辑学分支。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003410": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003410",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">在日常语言中，道义模态词的表述形式是多种多样的，例如：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003411": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003411",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（1）义务：应该，必须，一定要，不得不，有……的义务，等等；</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003412": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003412",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（2）允许：可以，准予，有权，等等；</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003413": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003413",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（3）禁止：不准，不得，不许，无权，等等。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003414": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003414",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">与模态词“必然”、“可能”、“不可能”等等一样，道义词既可以加在简单命题上面，也可以加在复合命题上面，修饰一个完整的命题，这时它们是“从言模态”；也可以插入量化命题的主谓词之间，修饰主词和谓词之间的联系方式，这时它们是“从物模态”。于是，道义命题有多种多样的表述方式。例如：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003415": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003415",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（4）公民应该依法纳税。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003416": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003416",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（5）允许大学生在校期间结婚。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003417": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003417",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（6）禁止在公共场所大声喧哗。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003418": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003418",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（7）允许人犯错误，但不允许人犯法。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003419": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003419",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（8）如果故意伤人，则应该负刑事责任。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003420": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003420",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（9）一个人应该做到：富贵不能淫，贫贱不能移，威武不能屈。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003421": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003421",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">我们用大写字母“O”（obligate）表示“义务”一类的道义词，用“P”（permit）表示“允许”一类的道义词，用“F”（forbid）表示“禁止”一类的道义词，则上述命题可以符号化为：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003422": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003422",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（4′）Op</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003423": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003423",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（5′）Pq</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003424": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003424",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（6′）Fr</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003425": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003425",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（7′）Pp∧<$image alt=\"alt\" class=\"tpzz\" source=\"$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/images/images/00002.jpeg\"></$image>Pq</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003426": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003426",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（8′）p→Oq</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003427": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003427",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（9′）O（p∧q∧r）</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003428": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003428",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext4\">我们还可以用“Op”或“Pp”去定义“Fp”：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003429": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003429",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">D1　Fp＝dfO<$image alt=\"alt\" class=\"tpzz\" source=\"$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/images/images/00002.jpeg\"></$image>p</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003430": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003430",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">D2　Fp＝df<$image alt=\"alt\" class=\"tpzz\" source=\"$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/images/images/00002.jpeg\"></$image>P<$image alt=\"alt\" class=\"tpzz\" source=\"$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/images/images/00002.jpeg\"></$image>p</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003431": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003431",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext4\">它们分别是说：“禁止p”等于说“应该非p”；“禁止p”等于说“不允许非p”。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003432": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003432",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">道义命题与模态命题有一个重要的差别。对于模态命题，下面两个蕴涵式成立：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003433": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003433",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（10）□p→p</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003434": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003434",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（11）p→◇p</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003435": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003435",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext4\">它们分别是说：从“必然p”可以推出p，从p可以推出“可能p”。这相当于说：凡是必然的都是现实的，凡是现实的都是可能的。这显然符合我们的直觉。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003436": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003436",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">但是，如果把（10）中“□”置换为“O”，把（11）“◇”置换为“P”，则下面两个蕴涵式不成立：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003437": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003437",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（12）Op→p</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003438": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003438",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（13）p→Pp</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003439": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003439",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext4\">它们分别是说：凡是应该做的事情都做了，凡是做了的事情都是允许做的。它们所刻画的是道德理想世界中的情形，而我们的现实世界肯定不是在道德上理想的：我们并没有做或没有能力去做许多应该做的事情；我们却做了一些在道德或法律上不允许做的事情。因此，有必要把上面两个公式弱化：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003440": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003440",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（14）O（Op→p）</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003441": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003441",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（15）O（p→Pp）</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003442": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003442",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext4\">它们分别是说：应该做的事情都做了，这是应该的；做的事情都是允许做的，这也是应该的。显然，这样的说法符合我们的直觉，是可以接受的。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003443": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003443",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">在经典命题逻辑的基础上，用“O”、“P”对其语言进行扩充，并增加与“O”、“P”相关的公理和推理规则，则可构成各种道义命题逻辑的系统。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003444": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003444",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\"><br class=\"calibre2\"></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003445": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003445",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">公理：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003446": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003446",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">　　A<sub class=\"calibre7\">0</sub>　所有经典命题逻辑的重言式</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003447": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003447",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">　　A<sub class=\"calibre7\">1</sub>　Pα↔<$image alt=\"alt\" class=\"tpzz\" source=\"$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/images/images/00002.jpeg\"></$image>O<$image alt=\"alt\" class=\"tpzz\" source=\"$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/images/images/00002.jpeg\"></$image>α</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003448": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003448",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">　　A<sub class=\"calibre7\">2</sub>　O（α→β）→（Oα→Oβ）</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003449": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003449",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">　　A<sub class=\"calibre7\">3</sub>　Oα→Pα</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003450": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003450",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">　　A<sub class=\"calibre7\">4</sub>　Oα→OOα</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003451": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003451",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">　　A<sub class=\"calibre7\">5</sub>　POα→Oα</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003452": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003452",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">　　A<sub class=\"calibre7\">6</sub>　O（Oα→α）</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003453": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003453",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">　　A<sub class=\"calibre7\">7</sub>　O（POα→α）</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003454": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003454",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">变形规则：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003455": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003455",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">　　MP：从α和α→β推出β</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003456": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003456",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">　　O-必然化规则：从α推出Oα</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003457": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003457",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\"><br class=\"calibre2\"></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003458": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003458",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext4\">这里，A<sub class=\"calibre8\">1</sub>说：“允许α”等值于“并非应该非α”；A<sub class=\"calibre8\">3</sub>说：如果“α→β”是应该的，那么，“应该α”蕴涵“应该β”；A<sub class=\"calibre8\">3</sub>说：“应该α”蕴涵“允许α”；A<sub class=\"calibre8\">4</sub>说，“应该α蕴涵“‘应该α’是应该的”；A<sub class=\"calibre8\">5</sub>说，“允许‘应该α’”蕴涵“应该α”；A<sub class=\"calibre8\">6</sub>说：“‘应该做的事情都做了’是应该的”；A<sub class=\"calibre8\">6</sub>说：“‘允许做应该做的事情都做了’是应该的”。O-必然化规则是说，若α是系统内的定理，则α是应该的。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003459": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003459",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">选取以上两个变形规则，并选取上面的某些公理，可以构造出10个不同的道义逻辑系统，分别定义如下：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003460": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003460",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\"><br class=\"calibre2\"></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003461": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003461",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">OK＝A<sub class=\"calibre7\">0</sub>～A<sub class=\"calibre7\">2</sub></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003462": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003462",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">OT＝A<sub class=\"calibre7\">0</sub>～A<sub class=\"calibre7\">2</sub>，A<sub class=\"calibre7\">6</sub></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003463": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003463",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">OS<sub class=\"calibre7\">4</sub>＝A<sub class=\"calibre7\">0</sub>～A<sub class=\"calibre7\">2</sub>，A<sub class=\"calibre7\">4</sub>，A<sub class=\"calibre7\">6</sub></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003464": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003464",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">OB＝A<sub class=\"calibre7\">0</sub>～A<sub class=\"calibre7\">2</sub>，A<sub class=\"calibre7\">6</sub>，A<sub class=\"calibre7\">7</sub></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003465": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003465",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">OS<sub class=\"calibre7\">5</sub>＝A<sub class=\"calibre7\">0</sub>～A<sub class=\"calibre7\">2</sub>，A<sub class=\"calibre7\">4</sub>，A<sub class=\"calibre7\">5</sub>（在OS<sub class=\"calibre7\">5</sub>中，A<sub class=\"calibre7\">6</sub>、A<sub class=\"calibre7\">7</sub>是定理）</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003466": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003466",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\"><br class=\"calibre2\"></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003467": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003467",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">令S是上述任一个系统，S<sub class=\"calibre8\">+</sub>可以定义如下：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003468": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003468",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\"><br class=\"calibre2\"></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003469": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003469",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">S<sub class=\"calibre7\">+</sub>＝S，A<sub class=\"calibre7\">3</sub></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003470": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003470",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\"><br class=\"calibre2\"></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003471": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003471",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">在OT以及比OT更强的道义逻辑系统中，下列道义命题对当方阵成立：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003472": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003472",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"picture\"><$image alt=\"alt\" class=\"calibre3\" source=\"$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/images/images/00071.jpeg\"></$image></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003473": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003473",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">根据这个对当方阵，各种道义命题之间有以下推理关系：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003474": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003474",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（16）“应该p”推出“不禁止p”；</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003475": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003475",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（17）“禁止p”推出“不应该p”；</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003476": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003476",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（18）“应该p”推出“允许p”；</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003477": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003477",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（19）“不允许p”推出“不应该p”；</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003478": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003478",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（20）“禁止p”推出“允许非p”；</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003479": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003479",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（21）“不允许非p”推出“不禁止p”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003480": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003480",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（22）“应该p”等值于“不允许非p”；</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003481": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003481",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（23）“禁止”等值于“不允许p”；</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003482": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003482",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（24）“允许p”等值于“不禁止p”；</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003483": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003483",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（25）“允许非p”等值于“不应该p”。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003484": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003484",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（26）“禁止p”等值于“应该非p”。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003485": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003485",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">仅举例说明（18）、（21）、（24）：从“子女应该赡养父母”推出“允许子女赡养父母”；从“不允许大学生不遵守法律”推出“不禁止大学生遵守法律”；“允许一部分人先富起来”与“不禁止一部分人先富起来”可以互推。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003486": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003486",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">道义逻辑的语义学仍然是可能世界语义学，只不过其中的可能世界是道德上可能的世界，道义命题的真值条件可以定义如下：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003487": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003487",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\"><br class=\"calibre2\"></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003488": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003488",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">Oα在道德可能世界w<sub class=\"calibre7\">i</sub>上是真的，当且仅当，α在所有比w<sub class=\"calibre7\">i</sub>在道德更为理想的世界w<sub class=\"calibre7\">j</sub>上是真的。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003489": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003489",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">Pα在道德可能世界w<sub class=\"calibre7\">i</sub>上是真的，当且仅当，α在有些比w<sub class=\"calibre7\">i</sub>在道德更为理想的世界w<sub class=\"calibre7\">j</sub>上是真的。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003490": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003490",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">Fα在道德可能世界w<sub class=\"calibre7\">i</sub>上是真的，当且仅当，α在所有比w<sub class=\"calibre7\">i</sub>在道德更为理想的世界W<sub class=\"calibre7\">j</sub>上是假的。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003491": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003491",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\"><br class=\"calibre2\"></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003492": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003492",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">根据这些语义定义，可以刻画道义命题之间的推理关系，也可以讨论相应的道义逻辑系统的元逻辑特性，如可靠性和完全性等。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003493": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003493",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"title1\">五　时态逻辑</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003494": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003494",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">时态逻辑是研究时态命题的逻辑特性及其推理关系的逻辑分支。它试图把涉及时间因素的命题之间的推理系统化，从而为涉及时间命题的精确讨论和严格推理提供工具。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003495": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003495",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">时态命题就是含有时态词的命题，其特点是：它们的真值依赖于说出它们的时间，随说出时间的不同而变化。例如：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003496": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003496",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（1）香港过去是英国的殖民地。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003497": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003497",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（2）中国正在崛起为世界大国。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003498": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003498",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（3）吴为将去英国牛津大学做访问学者。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003499": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003499",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">如果我们用大写字母“P”（past）表示“过去”，用“F”（future）表示“将来”，“现在p”则直接写成p，则上面三个命题可以符号化为：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003500": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003500",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（1′）Pp</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003501": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003501",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（2′）q</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003502": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003502",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（3′）Fr</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003503": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003503",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">利用P和F的组合，我们可以把其他时态命题符号化。例如：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003504": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003504",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（4）余涌已经是中国著名大学的教授。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003505": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003505",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext4\">可以表示为PPp，在英文中是现在完成时态。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003506": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003506",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（5）焦国威那时将已经获得博士学位。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003507": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003507",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext4\">可以表示为：FPp，在英文中是将来完成时态。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003508": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003508",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">在此基础上，再加上真值联结词<$image alt=\"alt\" class=\"tpzz\" source=\"$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/images/images/00002.jpeg\"></$image>、∧、∨、→、↔，我们就能表示其他的包含时态因素的命题。例如：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003509": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003509",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（6）小李今年下半年将结婚，但现在还没有房子。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003510": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003510",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（7）印度在2008年奥运会上或者将获得金牌，或者将获得银牌，或者将获得铜牌。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003511": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003511",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（8）如果你将来想做政治家，那么你现在要多参加社会活动。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003512": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003512",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext4\">可以分别符号化为：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003513": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003513",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（6′）Fp∧q</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003514": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003514",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（7′）Fp∨Fq∨Fr</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003515": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003515",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（8′）Fp→q</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003516": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003516",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">在时态逻辑中，我们还可以通过定义，引入两个新的时态词：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003517": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003517",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\"><br class=\"calibre2\"></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003518": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003518",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">D1　Gp＝<sub class=\"calibre7\">df</sub><$image alt=\"alt\" class=\"tpzz\" source=\"$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/images/images/00002.jpeg\"></$image>F<$image alt=\"alt\" class=\"tpzz\" source=\"$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/images/images/00002.jpeg\"></$image>p</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003519": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003519",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">D2　Hp＝<sub class=\"calibre7\">df</sub><$image alt=\"alt\" class=\"tpzz\" source=\"$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/images/images/00002.jpeg\"></$image>P<$image alt=\"alt\" class=\"tpzz\" source=\"$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/images/images/00002.jpeg\"></$image>p</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003520": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003520",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\"><br class=\"calibre2\"></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003521": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003521",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext4\">它们的意思是：“将要永远p”等于说“并非将要非p”，“过去一直p”等于说“并非过去非p”。于是，以下两个命题：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003522": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003522",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（9）地球将要永远围绕太阳转。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003523": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003523",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（10）太阳过去一直是从东方升起。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003524": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003524",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext4\">可以分别符号化为：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003525": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003525",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（9′）Gp</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003526": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003526",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">（10′）Hq</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003527": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003527",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">如果一个命题是永远为真的，则可以用“Hp∧p∧Gp”（即过去一直p，并且现在p，并且将要永远p）来表示。逻辑真理和数学真理大概是永恒的，于是我们有：“H（2＋2＝4）∧（2＋2＝4）∧G（2＋2＝4）”，“H（p∨<$image alt=\"alt\" class=\"tpzz\" source=\"$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/images/images/00002.jpeg\"></$image>p）∧（p∨<$image alt=\"alt\" class=\"tpzz\" source=\"$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/images/images/00002.jpeg\"></$image>p）∧G（p∨<$image alt=\"alt\" class=\"tpzz\" source=\"$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/images/images/00002.jpeg\"></$image>p）”。</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003528": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003528",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">在经典命题逻辑的基础上，加入新的初始符号，如G、H、F、P，新的常项1（真）和0（假），加入新的公式，例如如果α是公式，则Gα、Hα、Fα、Pα是公式，加入新的公理和变形规则，就可以得到不同的时态逻辑系统，它们刻画了时间关系的不同特性。下面给出一组时态逻辑系统的公理和推理规则，由它们可以构造不同的时态逻辑系统：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003529": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003529",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\"><br class=\"calibre2\"></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003530": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003530",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">公理：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003531": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003531",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><table class=\"calibre9\">\n  <tr class=\"calibre10\">\n    <td class=\"calibre11\">A<sub class=\"calibre8\">0</sub></td>\n    <td class=\"calibre11\">所有古典命题逻辑的重言式</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr class=\"calibre10\">\n    <td class=\"calibre11\">A<sub class=\"calibre8\">1</sub></td>\n    <td class=\"calibre11\">（a）G（α→β）→（Gα→Gβ）</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr class=\"calibre10\">\n    <td class=\"calibre11\"></td>\n    <td class=\"calibre11\">（b）H（α→β）→（Hα→Hβ）</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr class=\"calibre10\">\n    <td class=\"calibre11\"></td>\n    <td class=\"calibre11\">（c）α→GPα</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr class=\"calibre10\">\n    <td class=\"calibre11\"></td>\n    <td class=\"calibre11\">（d）α→HFα</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr class=\"calibre10\">\n    <td class=\"calibre11\">A<sub class=\"calibre8\">2</sub></td>\n    <td class=\"calibre11\">（a）Gα→GGα</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr class=\"calibre10\">\n    <td class=\"calibre11\"></td>\n    <td class=\"calibre11\">（b）Hα→HHα</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr class=\"calibre10\">\n    <td class=\"calibre11\">A<sub class=\"calibre8\">3</sub></td>\n    <td class=\"calibre11\">（a）（Fα∧Fβ）→（α∧Fβ）∨F（α∧β）∨（β∧Fα）</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr class=\"calibre10\">\n    <td class=\"calibre11\"></td>\n    <td class=\"calibre11\">（b）（Pα∧Pβ）→（α∧Pβ）∨P（α∧β）∨（β∧Pα）</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr class=\"calibre10\">\n    <td class=\"calibre11\">A<sub class=\"calibre8\">4</sub></td>\n    <td class=\"calibre11\">（a）G0∨FG0</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr class=\"calibre10\">\n    <td class=\"calibre11\"></td>\n    <td class=\"calibre11\">（b）H0∨PH0</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr class=\"calibre10\">\n    <td class=\"calibre11\">A<sub class=\"calibre8\">5</sub></td>\n    <td class=\"calibre11\">（a）Gα→Fα</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr class=\"calibre10\">\n    <td class=\"calibre11\"></td>\n    <td class=\"calibre11\">（b）Hα→Pα</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr class=\"calibre10\">\n    <td class=\"calibre11\">A<sub class=\"calibre8\">6</sub></td>\n    <td class=\"calibre11\">（a）Fα→FFα</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr class=\"calibre10\">\n    <td class=\"calibre11\"></td>\n    <td class=\"calibre11\">（b）Pα→PPα</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr class=\"calibre10\">\n    <td class=\"calibre11\">A<sub class=\"calibre8\">7</sub></td>\n    <td class=\"calibre11\">（a）α∧Hα→FHα</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr class=\"calibre10\">\n    <td class=\"calibre11\"></td>\n    <td class=\"calibre11\">（b）α∧Gα→PGα</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr class=\"calibre10\">\n    <td class=\"calibre11\">A<sub class=\"calibre8\">8</sub></td>\n    <td class=\"calibre11\">（a）Fα∧FG<$image alt=\"alt\" class=\"tpzz\" source=\"$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/images/images/00002.jpeg\"></$image>α→F（HFα∧G<$image alt=\"alt\" class=\"tpzz\" source=\"$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/images/images/00002.jpeg\"></$image>α）</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr class=\"calibre10\">\n    <td class=\"calibre11\"></td>\n    <td class=\"calibre11\">（b）Pα∧PH<$image alt=\"alt\" class=\"tpzz\" source=\"$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/images/images/00002.jpeg\"></$image>α→P（GPα∧H<$image alt=\"alt\" class=\"tpzz\" source=\"$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/images/images/00002.jpeg\"></$image>α）</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr class=\"calibre10\">\n    <td class=\"calibre11\">A<sub class=\"calibre8\">9</sub></td>\n    <td class=\"calibre11\">（a）H（Hα→α）→Hα</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr class=\"calibre10\">\n    <td class=\"calibre11\">A<sub class=\"calibre8\">10</sub></td>\n    <td class=\"calibre11\">（a）FGα→GFα</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr class=\"calibre10\">\n    <td class=\"calibre11\"></td>\n    <td class=\"calibre11\">（b）PHα→HPα</td>\n  </tr>\n</table></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003532": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003532",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">变形规则：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003533": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003533",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">　　MP：从α和α→β推出β</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003534": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003534",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">　　TG：从α推出Gα和Hα</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003535": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003535",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\"><br class=\"calibre2\"></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003536": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003536",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\">这里，不同的时态逻辑公理刻画了时间的不同性质。由这些公理和推理规则可以定义出一批时态逻辑系统L<sub class=\"calibre8\">n</sub>：</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003537": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003537",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext1\"><br class=\"calibre2\"></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003538": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003538",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">A<sub class=\"calibre7\">0</sub>＋A<sub class=\"calibre7\">1</sub>（a－d）＋MP＋TG＝K<sub class=\"calibre7\">t</sub>＝L<sub class=\"calibre7\">0</sub></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003539": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003539",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">L<sub class=\"calibre7\">0</sub>＋A<sub class=\"calibre7\">2</sub>（a）＝L<sub class=\"calibre7\">1</sub></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003540": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003540",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">L<sub class=\"calibre7\">1</sub>＋A<sub class=\"calibre7\">3</sub>（a，b）＝L<sub class=\"calibre7\">2</sub></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003541": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003541",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">L<sub class=\"calibre7\">1</sub>＋A<sub class=\"calibre7\">3</sub>（b）＝L<sub class=\"calibre7\">树</sub></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003542": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003542",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">L<sub class=\"calibre7\">2</sub>＋A<sub class=\"calibre7\">4</sub>（a，b）＝L<sub class=\"calibre7\">3</sub></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003543": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003543",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">L<sub class=\"calibre7\">2</sub>＋A<sub class=\"calibre7\">5</sub>（a，b）＝L<sub class=\"calibre7\">4</sub></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003544": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003544",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-767506b8c19e4254-43189b twpub-767506b8c19e4254-9882b5\"><p class=\"normaltext3\">L<sub class=\"calibre7\">0</sub>＋A<sub class=\"calibre7\">6</sub>（a）或A<sub class=\"calibre7\">6</sub>（b）＝L<sub class=\"calibre7\">5</sub></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/767506b8c19e4254/text/000003545": {
            "role": "text",
